# Vue practices

For substantive work on **Vue SFCs** (`.vue`), **read the relevant skill(s)** under `.cursor/skills/` before implementing.

## Baseline (most `.vue` changes)

1. Read `.cursor/skills/vue-best-practices/SKILL.md` first.

## Add by task

| Situation | Skill path |
|-----------|------------|
| Vue Router (routes, guards, navigation) | `.cursor/skills/vue-router-best-practices/SKILL.md` |
| Pinia (stores, state/actions) | `.cursor/skills/vue-pinia-best-practices/SKILL.md` |
| Options API components | `.cursor/skills/vue-options-api-best-practices/SKILL.md` |
| JSX / render functions (non-SFC) | `.cursor/skills/vue-jsx-best-practices/SKILL.md` |
| Composables (structure, reuse) | `.cursor/skills/create-adaptable-composable/SKILL.md` |
| Tests (Vitest, Vue Test Utils) | `.cursor/skills/vue-testing-best-practices/SKILL.md` |
| Tricky reactivity / lifecycle / edge cases | `.cursor/skills/vue-debug-guides/SKILL.md` |

## Visual / UI design

If the task is **visual or layout-heavy** (not only logic), also follow `.cursor/rules/frontend-design-ui.mdc` (it points at `frontend-design`).

## Composables-only `.ts` work

If there is **no** `.vue` file in context but the change is Vue-specific (e.g. under `composables/`), still read **`vue-best-practices`** and **`create-adaptable-composable`** when applicable.